{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"92676de0-c3fb-4040-8850-349ca57f3029","content":"Here's what you need to do:\n\n1. **Update packages** — replace `xunit.runner.visualstudio` with `xunit.runner.microsoft.testing.platform`:\n\n   ```xml\n   <!-- Remove -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.visualstudio\" Version=\"...\" />\n\n   <!-- Add -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.microsoft.testing.platform\" Version=\"2.9.3\" />\n   ```\n\n2. **Enable MTP** in your project file (or `Directory.Build.props`):\n\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n3. **Set the output type** to `Exe` (MTP test projects are self-contained executables):\n\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n4. **Run tests** — you can now use either:\n   - `dotnet test` (works as before)\n   - `dotnet run` (runs the test project directly)\n\n**Key notes:**\n- Keep `xunit` (or `xunit.core` + `xunit.assert`) at **2.9.3** — the runner version should match.\n- `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` ensures `dotnet test` routes through MTP instead of VSTest.\n- If you use any VSTest-specific adapters/settings (e.g., `.runsettings`), review them — MTP uses its own configuration model.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"fc138147-4526-42b7-bf0c-bba402c8992a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration path.","outputTokens":454,"requestId":"0BE9:2590B5:1D7D65:22A83D:69F0042D"},"id":"fca0e76c-3c4b-41a7-a5ed-f2d8ffa05e49","timestamp":"2026-04-28T00:49:59.335Z","parentId":"8016ad6b-3107-4d59-ac28-aebe0f55d514"}
